# Trades-Canada Free-First Workflow

Use this workflow by default for local development and validation:

1. Prefer built-in local checks before any external integration:

   - `pnpm check:web`
   - `pnpm dev:web`

1. Keep autonomous features functional without paid APIs:

   - Lead qualification must gracefully fall back when `OPENAI_API_KEY` is missing.
   - Never block lead intake if AI provider is unavailable.

1. Source-of-truth operational rules:

   - Stripe webhook source of truth is `apps/web/src/app/api/webhooks/stripe/route.ts`.
   - Keep `SUPABASE_ENABLE_LEGACY_STRIPE_WEBHOOK=false` unless doing emergency fallback.

1. Lead safety rules:

   - Keep anti-spam checks enabled in `/api/leads` (rate limit, honeypot, fill-time gate).
   - Never expose service role keys in client code or committed SQL.

1. Quebec-first product quality:

   - Preserve EN/FR parity for all user-facing copy.
   - Prioritize city/service matching and score-based lead routing for contractor visibility.
